In KZN, Warner Beach, Amanzimtoti, isiPingo, the Bluff and South Beach are teeming with shoals, as the annual migration spectacle kicks off. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - Keep a safe social distance -- just one of the COVID-19 regulations we know well. But the sardines are not playing by the rules. READ: We tracked SA's sardine run over 66 years: here's what we found In KwaZulu-Natal, Warner Beach, Amanzimtoti, isiPingo, the Bluff and South Beach are teeming with shoals as the annual migration spectacle kicks off. The sardine run has brought some relief to anglers, communities and businesses amid the lockdown's impact on the economy and tourism.